OL,3,CElectric vehicle drivers face London
OL,4,Ccongestion charge for first time
OL,6,FThe congestion charge, introduced in
OL,7,F2003, covers an area of central London
OL,8,Fbetween 7am and 6pm on weekdays, and
OL,9,Fbetween noon and 6pm on weekends and
OL,10,Fbank holidays.
OL,12,FPure battery-powered EVs had been
OL,13,Feligible for a 100% discount, but from
OL,14,FFriday this was reduced to 25% for
OL,15,Fcars, and 50% for vans and lorries.
OL,17,FThe EV discount will be cut further
OL,18,Ffrom March 4 2030, to 12.5% for cars
OL,19,Fand 25% for vans and lorries.
